    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1253"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1253">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1361</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-05">
                        <hi rend="italic">January 5, 1915</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>227. Your 191, December 21. From London Embassy, 2d. <persName corresp="#p_GSE1"
                        >Grey</persName> requests expression of his gratitude conveyed to you.</p>
                <p>Regarding specific demands Minister of Interior, <persName corresp="#p_GSE1"
                        >Grey</persName> requests you to point out to <persName corresp="#p_BT1"
                        >Talaat Bey</persName> that, though railroad line was shelled for obvious
                    military reasons, Alexandretta has not been bombarded. British Admiralty have no
                    intention employing force for any purpose beyond recognized legitimate usages of
                    war. Inform Ottoman Government release of Prince Omar Tousson and other Ottoman
                        <pb facs="1105" n="791" xml:id="pg_791"/> subjects mentioned will be
                    accorded under certain reasonable necessary conditions. British Government hope
                    therefore British subjects will be released and permitted to leave the country
                    if they so desire.</p>
                <p>You may communicate the above without comment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
